    {
      "id": "1b44750c-f3ba-8009-b24e-fefc5b284ce6",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "In online teaching, KT is meant to inform whether a teaching strategy should be changed according to the changes in learners knowledge states. Most KT models assume a binary target, without additional adjustments. For example, MCQ options introduce confounding concepts and, depending on the learner’s answer, it may be possible to understand the current knowledge state. ",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "1b44750c-f3ba-8009-b24e-fefc5b284ce6",
        "parent": {
          "type": "page_id",
